{
  "texts": [
    "We perform an exact case-agnostic match, and with the default setting having just two keywords: ['question', 'answer'].",
    "This heuristic is conservative -it only flips a label from malicious to benign in cases that are clearly safe upon manual inspection.",
    "Empirically this reduces the false positive rate on benign-only inputs.",
    "In deployment, these rules can be refined as needed.Finally, any segments marked as malicious (after post-processing) are removed from the input, or a run-time exception is raised, depending on the configuration.",
    "Implementation-wise, we reconstruct the sanitized prompt X by concatenating all segments s i for which the final label y i = 0."
  ]
}